.TH "intel_prepare_plane_fb" 9 "intel_prepare_plane_fb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_prepare_plane_fb \- Prepare fb for usage on plane
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" intel_prepare_plane_fb
.BI "(struct drm_plane *_plane "  ","
.BI "struct drm_plane_state *_new_plane_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "_plane" 12
drm plane to prepare for
.IP "_new_plane_state" 12
the plane state being prepared
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Prepares a framebuffer for usage on a display plane.  Generally this
involves pinning the underlying object and updating the frontbuffer tracking
bits.  Some older platforms need special physical address handling for
cursor planes.

Returns 0 on success, negative error code on failure.
